# Realtime Transport Conventions

- Canonical WebSocket path is `/api/v1/ws`. Keep `/ws` only as a legacy compatibility alias unless explicitly removed everywhere.
- WebSocket auth currently uses `?token=<access_token>`. If reconnect logic changes, it must re-read the latest token instead of caching a stale one.
- Group-scoped realtime events must include `group_id`.
- Client commands use imperative names like `status_change`; server events use past-tense names like `status_changed`.
- New connections must receive a `presence_snapshot` bootstrap before relying on incremental events.
- Cross-replica fan-out must publish through Redis; do not rely on in-process broadcast alone for staging/prod behavior.
- App lifespan must start the Redis pub/sub subscriber path when realtime delivery depends on it.
- Flutter presence state should hydrate from REST/bootstrap data and then apply WebSocket events incrementally.
- Any contract change here also requires updating `docs/specs/2026-05-30-real-time-coordination-design.md`.
